Broken access control is when users can see or do more than they are supposed to.
It happends when there is too much trust in the server or the client side. Let's say an application uses an ID number for a user profil in a URL and you can change that number in the URL to get data from another profile

Weak authorization : application fails to  protect sensitive content. Ex:Protecting admin page using a readable cookie

